e is turned inward as a form of self-punishment for being a holdout against God. Sorrow's Rigging is a study of panic at the death of hope expressed in novels born of the terrors writers cannot escape, yet in the very act of writing they redeem the world through art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aDespair in literature. 0aMeaning (Philosophy) in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358720540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773587205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773587205/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles